  "action_title": "Use nest covers to reduce the impact of research on predation of ground-nesting seabirds",
  "key_messages": "Key Messages:\nA before-and-after study in Canada found that protecting Caspian tern Sterna caspia nests after researchers disturbed parents from them significantly increased hatching success. This was due to a reduction in predation by ring-billed gulls Larus delawarensis."
}

